result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.descr: Records of prosec. are converted data. See file.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Chanse M Lenzner in court with attorney Brent Harold Debord.  Defendant Chanse M Lenzner in custody.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 16CF37, 15CF104 and 15CF202 @ 10:18 a.m. Agreement stated - 15CF202 dismiss and read in in 15CF104. 16CF 37 - dismiss without prejudice. 15CF104 - Def will plead to cts 1  & 2, cts 3 & 4 dismiss and read in, withheld sentence, 3 yrs probation, AODA and follow through, court costs, 6 months jail with credit only if revoked, amt tbd. 30 days to commence, huber as approved by jail, Def may be released today.  Atty Debord and Def agree. Plea quest. reviewed.  15CF104 ct 1 - no contest plea, ct 2 - no contest plea. Based on pleas 15CF202 dismissed and read in all cts, 15CF104 cts 3 & 4 dismiss and read in, 16CF37 dismissed without prejudice. Constitutional rights, elements, possible penalties reviewed. Atty Debord satisfied. Court finds Def understands and pleas freely & voluntarily made. Factual basis. Court accepts pleas and finds guilty of 15CF104 cts 1 & 2. Sentencing remarks by Counsel. Statement by Defendant. Remarks by the Court. Will approve agreement. Ct 1 - sentence withheld, 3 yrs probation, AODA and follow through, counseling as required, court costs, DNA sample and surcharge, 6 months jail, huber, credit if revoked held open, report no later than 6 p.m. on 4/10/16. Return $250 bond to poster. Def advised of voting and firearms restrictions. Ct 2 - sentence withheld, 3 yrs probation, same conditions as ct 1, AODA, counseling, court costs, DNA surcharge, 6 months jail, concurrent.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Postconviction rights. Statement by Atty Debord regarding Def's belongings when taken into custody. Def to address with Sheriff's Dept. $100 bond in 15CF202 to be applied to costs in 15CF104.

Defendant Chanse M Lenzner in court with attorney Michael K. DeBord.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 15CF104 and 15CF202 @ 11:34 a.m. Atty Debord appears specially today on 15CF202.  15CF104 - Arraignment - Information received, reading waived, not guilty pleas. Court receives pleas of not guilty to cts 1-4. Request status conference 1/4/16 @ 3:30 p.m. Def may attend but not required. However, advised to stay in contact w/Atty. Bond remains, Court reviews conditions. 15CF202 - Waiver of prelim filed. Court reviews prelim rights. Finds waiver as knowingly & voluntarily made. Binds over. Information filed. Copy received, reading waived, reserve all juris. objections, not guilty pleas. Court receives pleas. Status Conf. set. Bond remains.  Status conference scheduled for January 4, 2016 at 03:30 pm.

Defendant Chanse M Lenzner in court with attorney Brent Harold Debord.  Defendant Chanse M Lenzner in custody.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 15CF104, 15CF202 @ 11:13 a.m. 15CF104 - Preliminary hrg. Dep. Greg Carter duly sworn on oath, testifies. Witness identifies Defendant. Stipulate prior conviction for purposes of this hrg only. Atty Debord objects to finding probable cause for the record. No arguments offered. Court finds probable cause, binds over. Information filed. Copy received. 15CF202- special appearance by Atty Debord. Adjourned initial appearance. Copy of complaint received. Def will waive time limits for prelim if matter can be scheduled soon. Off the record for scheduling 11:33. Back on the record @ 11:35. Prelim 12/10/15 @ 11:30 a.m. Atty Debord heard on bond. Response by State. Court will lower bond to $100 cash.  Arraignment scheduled for December 10, 2015 at 11:30 am.
